data.title: Is it true that the Russian winter is no longer so harsh as it used to be?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 3): Russia is too big for me to speak about changes in its climate. As for the climate of the Moscow region where I’ve happened to live for several decades already, winters weren’t milder, but were very atypical.
